  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kano Literacy and Numeracy Accelerator (KaLMA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kano Literacy and Numeracy Accelerator aims to build foundational Hausa and English literacy and numeracy skills for 51,711 primary children in all schools in Wudil and Dawakin Tofa Local Governments using the Teaching at the Right Level approach, equipping them with foundational literacy and numeracy skills before they leave primary school.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kano Literacy and Numeracy Accelerator targets children in primary 4 to primary 6, who are assessed one-on-one by their teachers using a simple oral reading and maths assessment at the beginning of the programme. The assessment results are used to group children based on their learning levels rather than by age or grade. For the first two hours of the school day, the children&apos;s teachers (having been trained in the Teaching at the Right Level approach by the project) will focus on developing children&#x2019;s foundational skills in these learning level groups using the methodology they learnt.</narrative>
  </description>
